# List of UK dialling codes covering Wales

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Jump to: navigation, search

This is a list of geographic **UK dialling codes covering Wales** that are
currently in use. Some exchanges cover both sides of the [Wales-England
border](/wiki/Wales-England_border "Wales-England border"). All geographic
telephone numbers in Wales are in the format (01xxx) xxxxxx, with the
exception of [Cardiff](/wiki/Cardiff "Cardiff") and the surrounding area which
is (029) xxxx xxxx.

##
Misconceptions[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_UK_dialling_codes_covering_Wales&action=edit&section=1
"Edit section: Misconceptions")]

Main article: [UK telephone code
misconceptions](/wiki/UK_telephone_code_misconceptions "UK telephone code
misconceptions")

It is a common misconception that the code for [Cardiff](/wiki/Cardiff
"Cardiff") is 02920, whereas in fact it is 029 followed by an eight-digit
local number. This is due to Cardiff previously having a 5 digit code (01222)
with six-digit local numbers, and to the fact that all of its local numbers
begin with _20_ until 2005. This problem is also widespread in cities with
other 02x codes such as [Coventry](/wiki/Coventry "Coventry"),
[London](/wiki/London "London"), [Portsmouth](/wiki/Portsmouth "Portsmouth")
and [Southampton](/wiki/Southampton "Southampton"), and in the region of
[Northern Ireland](/wiki/Northern_Ireland "Northern Ireland").
